'''Cleaning droids''' or '''custodial droids''' were a type of [[droid]] whose purpose was to maintain cleanliness. During the [[Imperial Era|reign]] of the [[Galactic Empire]], a cleaning droid cleaned the [[Viewport|windows]] of some houses on [[Level 3204]], including those of the [[Milon family apartment|apartment]] belonging to [[Anandra Milon]]'s family.<ref name="OTLD">{{InsiderCite|151|One Thousand Levels Down}}</ref>

[[Infiltrator demolition droid]]s could disguise themselves as [[sweeper droid]]s for the purpose of covert operations.<ref name="Heroes on Both Sides">{{TCW|Heroes on Both Sides}}</ref> Custodial droids were used to perform minor tasks aboard the [[starship]] ''[[Legacy Run]]''. [[Hedda Casset]] noticed one such droid shortly before her ship's destruction.<ref name="Light of the Jedi">''[[The High Republic: Light of the Jedi]]''</ref>

{{Droid-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
Custodial droids appeared in the [[2021]] novel ''[[The High Republic: Light of the Jedi]]''.<ref name="Light of the Jedi" /> An early excerpt of the novel used the term "custodiodroid" instead.<ref name="IGN excerpt">{{WebCite|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/read-the-first-chapter-of-star-wars-the-high-republic-light-of-the-jedi-by-charles-soule|text=Read the First Chapter of Star Wars: The High Republic - Light of the Jedi by Charles Soule|author=Yehl, Joshua|date=2020-06-22|work=[https://www.ign.com IGN]|archiveurl=https://archive.is/r9ySz}}</ref>

